{"article_id":"NHIzP9JEOw9UeykR","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"On Front Lines Against Ebola ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Training A Matter Of Life Or Death","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"One of the biggest roadblocks in West Africa","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"to containing the Ebola outbreak","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"is the lack of isolation wards for people","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"who are infected .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"President Obama has announced plans","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"to build 17 new Ebola Treatment Units in Liberia .","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"Those new medical facilities will require thousands of additional workers","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"who are trained","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"and willing to work in them .","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"Without health care workers","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"who are n't scared to work ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"we are n't going to be able to do anything","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"[ toward ] combating the virus and its ongoing spread .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"In Monrovia , efforts are also underway","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"to start training local doctors , nurses and janitors on how to safely take care of patients","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"who are sick with the deadly disease .","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"The World Health Organization has taken over a two-story concrete hotel there","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"and transformed the ground floor into a mock Ebola treatment unit .","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"On a recent day , trainees","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"dressed in white Tyvek suits , gloves , goggles and face masks","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"were trying to restrain an Ebola patient","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"thrashing around on the ward .","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"In the process , several of them get splattered with blood .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"The blood is fake ,","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"but the process feels incredibly real ;","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"one of the trainees even runs out of the room .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"The exercise is part of a one-week course","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"to try to get new workers ready to handle the challenges of an Ebola ward .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Dr. Srinivas Murthy , an infectious disease specialist from the University of British Columbia , is one of the WHO staff","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"guiding the trainees .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"`` Who got sprayed with blood ? ''","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"Murthy asks .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"`` If you 're actively doing something else ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"you can continue to do those things .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"And then","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"when the hygienist is available","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"and you have a moment ,","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"you can have it sprayed down . `","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"` But to panic","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"when you have an exposure","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"is not the right thing to do","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"because , remember ,","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"whenever you 're not calm ,","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"problems happen , ''","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"he says .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"These trainees are on their last day of the course .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"They 'll spend the following week shadowing the staff inside a real Ebola ward","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"before they 're certified","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"to work in the new treatment units .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"Murthy says","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"teaching this group how to protect themselves around highly infectious patients is the most important lesson of the course .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"`` Without health care workers","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"who are motivated to work ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"and without health care workers","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"who are n't scared to work ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"we are n't going to be able to do anything","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"[ toward ] combating the virus and its ongoing spread , ''","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"he says .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"WHO hopes to be able to train several thousand new workers in the coming months .","depth":4},{"id":61,"text":"This is the second group of trainees","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"to go through the course .","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"Of the 72 people in the class , 40 of them are health care workers of some sort :","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"doctors , nurses , physicians ' assistants and even medical students .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"The rest are hygienists","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"who will be in charge of cleaning and disinfecting the Ebola wards .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"All of them are Liberian ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"and all of them have to work in head-to-toe protective gear .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"As they move through the mock Ebola treatment unit or ETU ,","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"many of them are having problems","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"with their goggles","depth":16},{"id":72,"text":"fogging up .","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"One doctor rips a glove","depth":15},{"id":74,"text":"and struggles to pull on another one over the torn latex .","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"Sweat drips around the edges of their surgical masks .","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"This group spends two hours","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"tending to `` patients '' in this staged ward .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"At the final station there 's a corpse","depth":16},{"id":79,"text":"- actually a leggy female mannequin -","depth":16},{"id":80,"text":"that needs to be put in a body bag .","depth":15},{"id":81,"text":"Everyone on the team is exhausted and overheated in their protective suits .","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"One of the hygienists starts disinfecting the corpse","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"before the doctor gets a chance","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"to confirm","depth":16},{"id":85,"text":"that she 's dead .","depth":16},{"id":86,"text":"An argument breaks out over who 's supposed to fetch the body bag .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"`` There 's no need for argument ;","depth":16},{"id":88,"text":"you are a hygienist , ''","depth":16},{"id":89,"text":"says Dr. Lucretia Kumauyah , a Liberian physician","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"who 's part of the training staff .","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"`` If they send you for a body bag ,","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"go and get it .","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"That should n't be an argument . ''","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"Kumauyah tries to keep the team focused on the task","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"of bagging the body","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"and carrying it to the morgue .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"She scolds them sternly about a breakdown in protocol over the protective suits .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"Several of the team members keep fiddling with their goggles ,","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"pulling them away from their faces ,","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"which could allow the virus to reach their eyes .","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"One of the nurses has let his surgical mask fall down so far","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"that his entire nose is exposed .","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"`` That 's the reason you can not enter the ETU alone , ''","depth":17},{"id":104,"text":"she says .","depth":17},{"id":105,"text":"`` You should always have someone","depth":17},{"id":106,"text":"observing you .","depth":17},{"id":107,"text":"You sweating ?","depth":16},{"id":108,"text":"If you can not make it ...","depth":17},{"id":109,"text":"what do we say ?","depth":18},{"id":110,"text":"Get out . ''","depth":18},{"id":111,"text":"After the team finally disposes of the body ,","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"they head to the exit ,","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"where they 're sprayed off with a chlorine solution .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Taking off the protective gear also must be done carefully","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"to make sure","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"there 's no exposure to the virus .","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"Dr. Patrick Lahai Kamara , one of the trainees , is soaked in sweat","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"as he steps out of the mock treatment unit .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"`` It 's not easy ;","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"it 's very hot , ''","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"he says .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"`` Little by little , we 'll get used to it . ''","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"Kamara just graduated from medical school last December .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"He 's been working at Redemption Hospital in Monrovia ,","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"but Redemption has n't been treating Ebola cases .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"Despite the fact","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"that almost a hundred health care workers in Liberia have died during this outbreak ,","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"Kamara says","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"he feels an obligation","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"to treat Ebola patients .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"`` Nobody is happy for what happened to the doctors","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"that have died , ''","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"he says .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"`` But it 's just like the soldiers ;","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"whenever there 's war in the country ,","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"the first people","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"you think","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"that will go","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"and fight for the nation","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"are the soldiers .","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"In time of health crisis ,","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"we physicians , we should be the ones on the front line . ''","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"If something goes wrong ,","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"he says ,","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"at least he died","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"fighting a just cause .","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"As more and more Ebola treatment units are built ,","depth":3},{"id":149,"text":"Liberia needs to find thousands of other workers","depth":4},{"id":150,"text":"who are also willing to take that risk .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":301,"left":152,"right":300,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":297,"right":299,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":210,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":209,"right":60,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":209,"left":196,"right":208,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":164,"right":195,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":164,"left":155,"right":163,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":153,"right":154,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":159,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":156,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":8,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":162,"left":160,"right":161,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":160,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":195,"left":178,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":176,"right":177,"relation":